      "writtenOn": "2017-07-24T17:30:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We need to tell power.skia.org which devices are associated with a given jumphost, otherwise it will give one command for a bunch of devices that aren\u0027t reachable from the same host, e.g. rpi-060-device and linux-001\n\nAdditionally, if we don\u0027t have something like this when running the powercycle command locally, we need to either 1) edit the /etc/powercycle.yaml to remove the unreachable devices after powercycle is pushed or 2) keep multiple powercycle.yaml files, one per jumphost.\n\nPrior to this CL, I had been doing 1) and I think this CL is cleaner than 2)\n\nI imagine if we migrate towards a more automated fix, we\u0027ll need to indicate to the powercycle daemons what rebootable devices work on their given machines.",
